# Pound cake
Butter pound cake by Sohlae

Pre-heat oven to 350 F.

## Cream butter
1. Beat butter, sugar, baking powder, and salt on medium-high until pale and very fluffy
- 196 grams | unsalted butter | room temperature
- 250 | granulated sugar
- 1/2 teaspoon | baking powder
- 1/2 teaspoon | kosher salt
 > Scrape down the paddle and sides of the bowl every 1-2 minutes. This should take 6-8mins total.

2. Add eggs one by one and let mix until incorporate - scraping down after every egg
 - 3 | eggs | room temperature
 - 1 | egg yolk | room temperature
 
## Adding dry ingredients
3. Mix sour cream and vanilla until lump-free in a separate bowl.
- 120 grams | sour cream | room temperature
- 1 teaspoon | vanilla extract

4. Add half of the sour cream, mix on low until incorporated. Add half of flour and mix until just incorporated. Repeat with the remaining sour cream and flour.
- 187 grams | all-purpose flour

5. Scrape the batter into a prepared pan and level the batter. 
> Swirl a knife or spatula through the batter to make sure it is evenly distributed.

6. Wet a butter knife and use it to slice down the center of the loaf cake.'

7. Bake until the crust is deeply browned. 60 - 70 minutes.

8. Cool the cake in the pan for 10 minutes.